# Fifty Years of Open Borders
## Restrictionists say the U.S. has had open borders since before most of us were born.

>**_The Short Stuff:_** For the past fifty years, restrictionists have consistently said that the United States either had "open borders",
or at best, had "lost control" of her borders.

### 2024
"Under Democratic influence since Ted Kennedy... the border has been essentially open to millions of people to come into this country illegally."
Dennis Prager, [Debate with Destiny](https://youtu.be/l7iz9PGI5jY?si=MruyPw3qdX_3ygTA&t=299) (4:49)

### 2022

"For all practical purposes, our borders are open."
Will Witt, [Who Cares About Illegal Immigration](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=izWK1EH0dag) (Video). Youtube, 12 Sept. 2022 (timestamp 4:29) 

### 2006 

"Republicans have supported open borders for decades."
Buchanan, Pat. *State of Emergency*. Thomas Dunne Books, 2006. Pg. 50

### 2004 

"In the end, the borders remain wide open. Most of the 2000-odd miles... are unmanned, unmonitored, and unprotected." 
Doughtery, Jon E. *Illegals: The Imminent Threat Posed by our Unsecured U.S.-Mexico Border*. 
Thomas Nelson Inc, 2004. Pg. vi

### 1999
America has never made a serious attempt to control its borders.
Daleiden, Joseph L. The American Dream: Can It Survive the 21st Century? Prometheus, 1 August 1999.

### 1990

"Firm commitment to enforcement of the immigration laws [has been] so far never conscientiously attempted in the United States."

Simcox, David. "Sustainable Immigration: Learning to Say No." "The Case for Fewer People" edited by Lindsey Grant. Negative Population Growth, 2006, pg. 101 
(Original article published March 1990)

### 1984  

"The simple truth is that we've lost control of our own borders, and no nation can do that and survive"

Reagan, Ronald. "Moving Briskly on Immigration Law Changes". The New York Times, 17 June 1984


### 1981 

"We are not in any way effectively enforcing [our immigration] laws... We have effectively lost control of our borders."

Smith, William French ["Firing Line with William F. Buckley Jr.: Where Do We Go on Immigration?"](https://youtu.be/6QaxprQEzpM?si=Wz6hn03d2w-7ZdDY&t=884). First broadcast 1 Oct. 1981. (timestamp 15:00)


